article.headline: Mississippi 77, Illinois-Chicago 64
article.story: OXFORD, Miss. (AP) -- Clarence Sanders scored 20 points to lead Mississippi to a 77-64 win over Illinois-Chicago on Tuesday. Ole Miss (10-2) held the Flames to a pair of baskets in the final five minutes, breaking open a tight 61-59 game with a 16-2 surge. Sanders scored 16 second-half points, including 13 in the decisive late run. Illinois-Chicago (6-6) led 27-26 at half time but faded offensively in the final minutes of the game. The teams changed leads six times before Sanders sunk a 3-pointer and put the Rebels ahead for good with 10:13 left. Bam Doyne scored 18 points, Dwayne Curtis chipped in 13 for the Rebels and grabbed 12 rebounds. Jermey Parnell added 11 points. Ole Miss shot 19-of-29 from the field in the second half, including 6-of-9 from 3-point range. T.J. Gray led Illinois-Chicago with 17 points and Othyus Jeffers added 14. The Flames were 11-of-27 from 3-point range, including five by Gray.
